<Layout title="Xavier Yin" lang="yue" altLangHref="/en/" altLangLabel="EN">
	<h1>Xavier Yin</h1>
	<p>
		[ˈzæj.vɪə ˈjɪn]
	</p>
	<p>
		我係一位來住新西蘭嘅博士生，喺Carnegie Mellon University (CMU) Language Technologies Institute (LTI)嘅<a href="https://lab-msp.com/">Multimodal Signal Processing (MSP)</a>研究室，
		師從<a href="https://carlosbusso.com/">Carlos Busso</a>教授。
		而家，我研究speech articulatory synthesis，特別係text-to-articulatory synthesis。
		來到CMU之前，我完成咗我嘅本科同碩士喺UC Berkeley，師從<a href="https://people.eecs.berkeley.edu/~gopala/">Gopala Anumanchipalli</a>教授。
		
		我碩士嘅論文係關於證實text-to-articulatory synthesis新方法喺語音研究。
		My master's thesis focused on the feasibility of text-to-articulatory synthesis as a
		novel approach for speech research. I've also worked on fairness and privacy in large language models
		including linguistic bias, standard language ideology, and data privacy risks.
	</p>
	<p>
		研究之外，我中意旅游、hiking同埋攀岩。
		我亦中意喺大自然影相，特別係拍雀啲相，有時會畫畫同作曲。
	</p>
	<p>
		你可以揾到我啲研究喺<a href="/research">Research</a> 頁面，
		與及我有時會發各種關於philosophy、theology、等話題啲寫作喺我<a href="/blog">Blog</a>度。
	</p>

	<h2>Mentorship</h2>
	<p>
		I'm not currently accepting mentee applicants directly (undergraduate or master's). If you're
		interested in working with me, please email <a href="mailto:busso@cmu.edu">Prof. Busso</a> directly
		and mention that you'd like to work with me.
	</p>

	<h2>Contact Me</h2>
	<p>
		I'm always happy to hear from other researchers working on related problems, or from anyone
		with questions about my published work. If you'd like to discuss a potential collaboration,
		invite me to speak or review, or simply have a chat, please send an email to:
	</p>
	<p>
		<a href="mailto:nzxyin@cmu.edu">nzxyin (at) cmu (dot) edu</a>
	</p>
	<p>
		&#127475;&#127487; To any Kiwis in the Pittsburgh area who want to meet up, feel free to reach out! I'm always happy to meet fellow New Zealanders.
	</p>
</Layout>
